        "fact_id": "loss_statement_changes_action",
        "status": "supported",
        "text": "Declared losses should constrain the recommended action rather than being appended as decorative text."
      }
    ],
    "conclusion": "Declared losses are not decorative footnotes; they are active constraints on what the artifact can claim and recommend. When calibration evidence is missing, the artifact must declare that absence, must not promote unsupported claims into supported ones, and must ensure the recommended action is visibly shaped by the limitation. These three principles together form a discipline: the loss statement, the evidence boundary, and the action constraint operate as a single integrity mechanism.",
    "declared_losses": [
      "missing calibration evidence"
    ],
    "recommended_action": "Adopt a standing rule that every research artifact include a \"Declared Losses\" section whose entries are directly referenced in the recommendation text. Specifically, when calibration evidence is missing, the recommendation must begin with: \"Pending calibration evidence, the following action is provisional...\" This ensures the limitation visibly constrains the action rather than sitting in an ignored appendix.",
    "task_id": "declared_loss_discipline"
  },
